=Richard B. Mather (1913-)=
===Keywords===
[[謝靈運]] [[世說新語]] [[沈約]]
==Publications==
===Monographs===
* Biography of Lü Kuang. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1959
* Shih-shuo hsin-yü: A New Account of Tales of the World. Minneapolis, 1976
* The Poet Shen Yüeh (441-513): The Reticent Marquis. Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1988
* The Age of Eternal Brilliance: Three Lyric Poets of the Yung-ming Era (483-493). Leiden: Brill, 2003
===Articles===
* The Landscape Buddhism in the Fifth Century Poet Hsieh Ling-yün. Journal of Asian Studies, Volume 18, 1958-59, pp. 67-79
* The Mystical Ascent of the T'ien-T'ai Mountains: Sun Ch'o's Yu T'ien-t'ai-shan fu. Monumenta Serica, Volume 20, 1961, pp. 226-245
* Wang Chin's Dhuta Temple Stele Inscription. Journal of the American Oriental Society, Volume 83, No. 3, 1963, pp. 338-359
* Chinese Letters and Scholarship in the Third and Fourth Centuries: The Wen-Hsüeh P'ien of the Shih-Shuo-Hsin-Yü. JAOS, Volume 84, No. 4, 1964, pp. 348-391
* Some Examples of 'Pure Conversation' in the Shih-shuo Hsin-yü. Transactions of International Conference of Orientalists in Japan 9 (1964):
* Vimalakīrti and Gentry Buddhism. History of Religions, Volume 8, No. 1, 1968, pp. 60-73
* The Controversy over Conformity and Naturalness during the Six Dynasties. History of Religions, Volume 9, No. 2/3, 1969/70, pp. 160-180
* The Fine Art of Conversation: The Yen-yü P'ien of the Shih-shuo hsin-yu. JAOS, Volume 91, No. 2, 1971, pp. 222-275
* Shen Yüeh's Poems of Reclusion: From Total Withdrawal to Living in the Suburbs. CLEAR, Volume 5, No. 1/2, 1983, pp. 53-66
* The Life of the Buddha and the Buddhist Life: Wang Jung's (468-93) "Songs of Religious Joy" (Fa-le tz'u). JAOS, Volume 107, No. 1, 1987, pp. 31-38